WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for Samsung's Exynos 2600 flagship mobile
SoC. Manufactured on Samsung's 2nm Gate-All-Around (GAA) process (SF2),
it is the world's first 2nm smartphone chipset, powering the Galaxy S26
series in 2026. This file documents the CPU microarchitecture, GPU
configuration, NPU AI accelerator, cognitive ISP, memory subsystem, and
imaging pipeline formulas.

WHY IT EXISTS
The Exynos 2600 represents Samsung's renewed commitment to in-house chip
development, achieving parity with Qualcomm's Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5 and
Apple's A19 Pro in both AI and imaging workloads. GIOP must provide a
certified profile to map the chip's ISP and NPU pipelines into an auditable,
ACES-compliant imaging workflow.

HOW IT WORKS
CPU Performance (C1 Custom Cores, Arm v9.2, 2nm GAA SF2):
  Single-core throughput:
    Perf(f) = IPC * f
    IPC uplift vs Cortex-X4: +36% (Geekbench 6.2)
    C1-Ultra Prime at 3.80 GHz → Perf ≈ 5.17 (normalised to X4 at 3.4 GHz = 3.4)
    C1-Pro at 3.26 GHz → Perf ≈ 4.43
    C1-Efficiency at 2.76 GHz → Perf ≈ 3.75
  Multi-core scaling (Amdahl):
    P(N) = 1 / ((1 – f_parallel) + f_parallel / N)
    where f_parallel = 0.92, N = 10 cores.

CPU Dynamic Power:
  P_cpu = C_eff * V^2 * f
  where C_eff ≈ 2.5 nF (C1-Ultra, 2nm GAA), V = 0.55–0.95 V, f = 2.76–3.80 GHz.
  Sustained TDP: 5.5 W (smartphone passive cooling).
  Thermal headroom: +30% vs Exynos 2500 (Samsung claims 30% less heat).

GPU Throughput (Xclipse 960, AMD RDNA 4):
  FP32 TFLOPS:
    TFLOPS_FP32 = (CUs * ALUs_per_CU * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
    = (10 * 128 * 2 * 1.25e9) / 1e12 ≈ 3.2 TFLOPS
  FP16 TFLOPS (packed math): 2× FP32 ≈ 6.4 TFLOPS
  Ray Tracing: hardware RT cores, 2.8 Giga-rays/s.
  Performance uplift vs Xclipse 950: +24%.

NPU AI Throughput (Dual-GNPU + Dual-SNPU):
  INT8 TOPS:
    TOPS_INT8 = (MAC_units * 2 * f_npu) / 1e12
    ≈ (24,576 * 2 * 2.0e9) / 1e12 ≈ 98 TOPS (marketed ~59 TOPS sustained)
  Uplift vs Exynos 2500 NPU: +39%.
  Generative AI performance (CPU+NPU combined): +113% vs Exynos 2500.
  On-device Stable Diffusion XL (1024×1024, 20 steps): ~1.5 s first pass.

ISP Throughput (Samsung Cognitive ISP, 20-bit):
  Pixel Rate:
    R_isp = f_isp * pixels_per_cycle
    = 1.4e9 * 16 = 22.4 Gpix/s
  Supports 320 MP single-shot, 8K 60 fps HDR video encode (HEVC/AV1).
  Real-time 12-layer semantic segmentation at 4K.
  Quad-exposure HDR fusion at 14-bit linear RAW.

Memory Bandwidth (LPDDR6x, 64-bit):
  BW = bus_width_bytes * f_data * 2(DDR)
  = 8 * 14.4e9 * 2 = 115.2 GB/s (per 64-bit channel)
  Max capacity: 24 GB.

